WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.019
Our missions conference is on the calendar

00:00:03.019 --> 00:00:05.260
and I believe that it's important

00:00:05.260 --> 00:00:07.039
as we think about missions conference

00:00:07.039 --> 00:00:10.060
that we seek to be prepared for missions conference.

00:00:10.060 --> 00:00:13.420
And honestly, missions conference is probably

00:00:13.420 --> 00:00:16.219
one of my favorite times of the calendar year.

00:00:16.219 --> 00:00:19.780
I enjoy revival meetings in the fall.

00:00:19.780 --> 00:00:21.979
They're obviously a huge blessing,

00:00:21.979 --> 00:00:23.180
a highlight on the calendar,

00:00:23.180 --> 00:00:26.540
but a missions conference is kind of a revival meeting,

00:00:26.540 --> 00:00:29.819
missions emphasis kind of all tied together

00:00:29.819 --> 00:00:31.620
and just absolutely love it.

00:00:31.620 --> 00:00:33.500
If you've never been part of a missions conference,

00:00:33.500 --> 00:00:35.020
I wanna encourage you to be here

00:00:35.020 --> 00:00:36.259
for the missions conference.

00:00:36.259 --> 00:00:38.459
I believe that you'll be encouraged and blessed.

00:00:38.459 --> 00:00:40.540
I know some have not been here

00:00:40.540 --> 00:00:42.099
as part of our missions conference.

00:00:42.099 --> 00:00:43.299
You're newer to our church

00:00:43.299 --> 00:00:45.500
and we wanna make sure that you're ready

00:00:45.500 --> 00:00:47.779
for what God has for us.

00:00:47.779 --> 00:00:51.020
And the preaching is stirring, it's convicting.

00:00:51.020 --> 00:00:53.340
We're challenged to have a portion,

00:00:53.340 --> 00:00:56.860
a part in what God is doing globally.

00:00:56.860 --> 00:00:59.860
I'm always reminded as we read our update letters

00:00:59.860 --> 00:01:00.700
from our missionaries,

00:01:00.700 --> 00:01:03.619
as I interact with our missionaries, I pray for them.

00:01:03.619 --> 00:01:07.580
I'm reminded that God is doing a work globally

00:01:07.580 --> 00:01:09.839
and I'm thankful for the work that God is doing.

00:01:09.839 --> 00:01:12.739
I'm thankful for the work that God is doing locally,

00:01:12.739 --> 00:01:16.500
but we understand that for God so loved the world

00:01:16.500 --> 00:01:19.419
and God is doing a work globally

00:01:19.419 --> 00:01:21.900
and I am extremely thankful

00:01:21.900 --> 00:01:24.580
that we have an opportunity to be a part

00:01:24.580 --> 00:01:26.260
in what God is doing.

00:01:26.620 --> 00:01:28.860
And I am persuaded that God's people

00:01:28.860 --> 00:01:31.319
should actively prepare,

00:01:31.319 --> 00:01:34.580
not only for every Sunday morning, every service,

00:01:34.580 --> 00:01:35.819
we ought to have prepared hearts,

00:01:35.819 --> 00:01:37.819
but we have these special meetings.

00:01:37.819 --> 00:01:41.139
It's important that we're prepared spiritually.

00:01:41.139 --> 00:01:42.900
Every time we have a missions conference,

00:01:42.900 --> 00:01:44.779
we'll give out some things this evening.

00:01:44.779 --> 00:01:46.099
Every time we have a revival meeting,

00:01:46.099 --> 00:01:48.660
we give you a little handout of some prayer points

00:01:48.660 --> 00:01:52.059
for the week and seeking to have your heart prepared,

00:01:52.059 --> 00:01:53.980
to have our hearts prepared

00:01:53.980 --> 00:01:56.459
and praying for those that will come and be with us.

00:01:56.459 --> 00:02:01.099
And so we desire to be ready for what God has for us.

00:02:01.099 --> 00:02:05.720
I believe this, that God, every time you open your Bible,

00:02:05.720 --> 00:02:07.940
whether it's in your daily devotions

00:02:07.940 --> 00:02:09.940
or if it's when you come to a church service,

00:02:09.940 --> 00:02:13.619
I believe every single time God has something for us.

00:02:13.619 --> 00:02:15.619
And we need to have hearts that are prepared

00:02:15.619 --> 00:02:19.059
to receive what God has for us

00:02:19.059 --> 00:02:21.940
and that we're actively seeking the Lord

00:02:21.940 --> 00:02:25.259
to have that heart that is a tender heart.

00:02:25.259 --> 00:02:27.380
You know, God speaks of Josiah,

00:02:27.380 --> 00:02:30.220
of a man that had a tender heart.

00:02:30.220 --> 00:02:32.860
The word of God was read and man,

00:02:32.860 --> 00:02:35.699
he responded to the word of God being read

00:02:35.699 --> 00:02:37.619
in a very appropriate way.

00:02:37.619 --> 00:02:40.059
And we need to have our hearts prepared.

00:02:40.059 --> 00:02:42.660
This morning, with really that thought in mind

00:02:42.660 --> 00:02:44.500
of having hearts prepared,

00:02:44.500 --> 00:02:46.820
I want us to consider a portion of scripture here

00:02:46.820 --> 00:02:48.860
in Acts chapter number 20,

00:02:48.860 --> 00:02:51.979
where the apostle Paul is speaking to the leaders

00:02:51.979 --> 00:02:54.020
of the church at Ephesus.

00:02:54.020 --> 00:02:58.139
And Paul has a desire to get to Jerusalem and on his way,

00:02:58.139 --> 00:03:00.919
he has a desire to meet with these leaders

00:03:00.919 --> 00:03:02.660
from the church at Ephesus.

00:03:02.660 --> 00:03:04.899
And as he calls them together,

00:03:04.899 --> 00:03:07.679
he shares many things with them.

00:03:07.679 --> 00:03:10.740
This morning, I'm gonna jump in the midst of the text,

00:03:10.740 --> 00:03:13.580
but we find that he begins speaking to them.

00:03:13.580 --> 00:03:14.979
It says that in verse 17,

00:03:14.979 --> 00:03:17.020
from Miletus he sent to Ephesus

00:03:17.020 --> 00:03:18.759
and called the elders of the church.

00:03:19.660 --> 00:03:21.960
And in verse 18, and when they were come to him,

00:03:21.960 --> 00:03:24.440
he said unto them,

00:03:24.440 --> 00:03:26.339
and he starts out by saying this,

00:03:26.339 --> 00:03:29.800
ye know from the first day that I came into Asia,

00:03:29.800 --> 00:03:33.720
after what manner I have been with you at all seasons.

00:03:33.720 --> 00:03:36.539
And the apostle Paul begins to talk about several things

00:03:36.539 --> 00:03:40.160
with regard to his service for the Lord there in Ephesus.

00:03:40.160 --> 00:03:43.559
And obviously as God would use him in other regions

00:03:43.559 --> 00:03:45.259
during his missionary journeys.

00:03:45.259 --> 00:03:48.699
But as he's speaking to this group of church leaders,

00:03:49.539 --> 00:03:51.460
I want you to pick it up with me in verse 26.

00:03:51.460 --> 00:03:52.460
The Bible says this,

00:03:52.460 --> 00:03:57.460
wherefore, wherefore I take you to record this day

00:03:58.820 --> 00:04:03.600
that I am pure from the blood of all men.

00:04:03.600 --> 00:04:07.580
For I have not shunned to declare unto you all

00:04:07.580 --> 00:04:09.580
the counsel of God.

00:04:09.580 --> 00:04:12.179
I have not shunned to declare unto you

00:04:12.179 --> 00:04:14.639
all the counsel of God.

00:04:14.639 --> 00:04:18.179
That word shunned in verse number 27 is very unique word.

00:04:18.179 --> 00:04:20.420
In fact, that word's only used four times

00:04:20.420 --> 00:04:21.940
in the entire New Testament,

00:04:21.940 --> 00:04:24.540
that Greek word there that's translated shunned.

00:04:24.540 --> 00:04:26.299
And on two of those four times,

00:04:26.299 --> 00:04:30.440
it's in this address to the leaders of the church at Ephesus

00:04:30.440 --> 00:04:33.799
and that word that is used and translated shunned,

00:04:33.799 --> 00:04:38.100
it carries with it the idea of those who from timidity

00:04:38.100 --> 00:04:42.980
hesitate to avow what they believe.

00:04:42.980 --> 00:04:46.660
To be unwilling to utter from fear,

00:04:46.660 --> 00:04:50.619
to shrink from declaring, to conceal.

00:04:50.619 --> 00:04:51.980
You notice that Paul says,

00:04:51.980 --> 00:04:55.820
for I have not shunned to declare unto you

00:04:55.820 --> 00:04:59.440
all the counsel of God.

00:04:59.440 --> 00:05:02.380
I've titled the message this morning from verse number 26,

00:05:02.380 --> 00:05:05.980
do I have blood on my hands?

00:05:05.980 --> 00:05:09.140
Do I have blood on my hands?

00:05:09.140 --> 00:05:11.200
Notice with me if you're taking notes this morning,

00:05:11.200 --> 00:05:14.299
number one, Paul's understanding,

00:05:14.299 --> 00:05:15.660
Paul's understanding.

00:05:15.660 --> 00:05:18.660
We must recognize at the onset of the message this morning

00:05:18.660 --> 00:05:21.100
that the Apostle Paul was well-trained.

00:05:21.100 --> 00:05:23.980
We find that the Apostle Paul would have been an expert

00:05:23.980 --> 00:05:26.779
in the Old Testament and he was trained,

00:05:26.779 --> 00:05:28.779
he was schooled, he understood.

00:05:28.779 --> 00:05:31.459
And many times even as he is dealing with

00:05:31.459 --> 00:05:33.339
and preaching and writing,

00:05:33.339 --> 00:05:35.540
you'll find there's a number of references

00:05:35.540 --> 00:05:38.779
that he gives to the Old Testament.

00:05:38.779 --> 00:05:42.100
And so understanding the fact that the Apostle Paul

00:05:42.100 --> 00:05:44.059
is an expert in the Old Testament,

00:05:44.820 --> 00:05:48.100
I conclude that his reference here in verse number 26,

00:05:48.100 --> 00:05:51.260
where he says that I'm pure from the blood of all men

00:05:51.260 --> 00:05:54.140
has its roots in the book of Ezekiel.

00:05:54.140 --> 00:05:55.540
So if you take your Bible and turn back

00:05:55.540 --> 00:05:57.700
to the book of Ezekiel, just briefly this morning,

00:05:57.700 --> 00:05:59.700
Ezekiel chapter number three,

00:05:59.700 --> 00:06:02.299
and I want you to notice there in the book of Ezekiel

00:06:02.299 --> 00:06:03.140
in the third chapter,

00:06:03.140 --> 00:06:05.579
you can look at the 33rd chapter as well,

00:06:05.579 --> 00:06:07.779
but we'll spend time here right in Ezekiel

00:06:07.779 --> 00:06:09.779
chapter number three.

00:06:09.779 --> 00:06:12.459
And I want you to understand some things here

00:06:12.459 --> 00:06:15.500
with regard to what Paul is referencing

00:06:15.500 --> 00:06:20.019
when he says that he's pure from the blood of all men.

00:06:20.019 --> 00:06:23.059
We find here in Ezekiel chapter number three,

00:06:23.059 --> 00:06:25.140
pick it up with me in verse number 16, if you will,

00:06:25.140 --> 00:06:28.660
Ezekiel chapter number three in verse number 16.

00:06:29.940 --> 00:06:32.420
And it came to pass at the end of seven days

00:06:32.420 --> 00:06:35.859
that the word of the Lord came unto me saying,

00:06:35.859 --> 00:06:39.700
son of man, I have made thee a watchman

00:06:39.700 --> 00:06:41.980
under the house of Israel.

00:06:41.980 --> 00:06:44.459
Therefore, hear the word at my mouth

00:06:44.459 --> 00:06:47.500
and give them warning from me.

00:06:47.500 --> 00:06:49.239
Now, let me just pause for a moment.

00:06:49.239 --> 00:06:50.859
As you study the scriptures here

00:06:50.859 --> 00:06:54.899
and you understand the responsibility of Ezekiel,

00:06:54.899 --> 00:06:57.420
you find that the Bible tells us in verse 17

00:06:57.420 --> 00:07:00.739
and verse 16 that the word of the Lord came unto me saying,

00:07:00.739 --> 00:07:04.779
and God comes to Ezekiel, he refers to him as son of man.

00:07:04.779 --> 00:07:06.100
And notice what God says,

00:07:06.100 --> 00:07:10.899
I, God, have made thee, Ezekiel, a watchman.

00:07:10.899 --> 00:07:13.100
Can I tell you in a very real way this morning,

00:07:13.100 --> 00:07:16.700
God has made us as his people watchmen.

00:07:16.700 --> 00:07:18.500
He has made us witnesses.

00:07:18.500 --> 00:07:20.279
It's not something that we see here

00:07:20.279 --> 00:07:22.579
where there was some kind of application

00:07:22.579 --> 00:07:24.980
that was sent out of who wants to be a watchman

00:07:24.980 --> 00:07:27.459
and Ezekiel filled that thing out and whatever,

00:07:27.459 --> 00:07:28.980
and he got the job.

00:07:28.980 --> 00:07:33.500
No, God says, I have set thee, Ezekiel, to be a watchman.

00:07:33.500 --> 00:07:35.480
And what is the responsibility?

00:07:35.480 --> 00:07:37.079
Well, we find here, it says this,

00:07:37.079 --> 00:07:39.500
he's a watchman under the house of Israel.

00:07:39.540 --> 00:07:44.100
Therefore, notice when he says, hear the word at my mouth,

00:07:44.100 --> 00:07:45.820
so he's gonna hear the word of God

00:07:45.820 --> 00:07:50.359
and give them warning from who, from me.

00:07:50.359 --> 00:07:53.239
So we find that Ezekiel would have this task,

00:07:53.239 --> 00:07:56.260
this responsibility of being a watchman.

00:07:56.260 --> 00:07:59.220
And really what he was responsible to do

00:07:59.220 --> 00:08:04.220
was to hear from God and faithfully declare to the people

00:08:04.519 --> 00:08:06.339
the warning from God.

00:08:06.339 --> 00:08:08.500
And we find that we could make application

00:08:08.500 --> 00:08:10.899
even see as Paul does in Acts chapter number 20

00:08:10.899 --> 00:08:12.739
with regard to this reference,

00:08:12.739 --> 00:08:16.739
that God, he says that ye shall be witnesses unto me.

00:08:16.739 --> 00:08:18.859
We understand that we are his witnesses.

00:08:18.859 --> 00:08:21.820
We understand that he's given us this responsibility

00:08:21.820 --> 00:08:25.980
to preach the gospel, that we're to go and warn every man.

00:08:25.980 --> 00:08:28.660
And we find that that warning is coming from God.

00:08:28.660 --> 00:08:31.619
It's that we're speaking the word of God

00:08:31.619 --> 00:08:33.780
to a lost and dying world.

00:08:33.780 --> 00:08:35.380
And so we find in verse 18,

00:08:35.380 --> 00:08:38.039
that God continues to explain to Ezekiel

00:08:38.580 --> 00:08:42.039
what this means, what is contained within the idea

00:08:42.039 --> 00:08:45.359
that I'm a watchman and what are the responsibilities.

00:08:45.359 --> 00:08:47.880
In verse 18, when I say unto the wicked,

00:08:47.880 --> 00:08:52.719
thou shalt surely die and thou givest him not warning.

00:08:52.719 --> 00:08:55.960
So notice in verse 18, he says that God says,

00:08:55.960 --> 00:08:59.960
I'm going to give this warning, but you don't do,

00:08:59.960 --> 00:09:04.960
you do not fulfill your responsibility as a watchman.

00:09:05.159 --> 00:09:10.159
He says, and thou givest him not warning,

00:09:10.559 --> 00:09:14.280
nor speakest to warn the wicked from his wicked way

00:09:14.280 --> 00:09:15.619
to save his life.

00:09:15.619 --> 00:09:19.359
The same wicked man shall die in his iniquity.

00:09:19.359 --> 00:09:23.159
But notice the content there at the end of verse 18,

00:09:23.159 --> 00:09:28.159
but his blood will I require at thine hand.

00:09:28.440 --> 00:09:31.280
Wow, that's significant.

00:09:31.280 --> 00:09:34.539
I mean, those are serious stakes.

00:09:35.059 --> 00:09:37.380
God says, I'm given the warning and your job,

00:09:37.380 --> 00:09:42.140
Ezekiel, as a watchman is to simply receive from me

00:09:42.140 --> 00:09:44.260
and then deliver to the people.

00:09:44.260 --> 00:09:47.380
And if you do not, remember Paul said there,

00:09:47.380 --> 00:09:49.780
as we looked at the text in Acts chapter number 20,

00:09:49.780 --> 00:09:53.219
that he did not shun from declaring.

00:09:53.219 --> 00:09:54.960
And we find here that he says,

00:09:54.960 --> 00:09:58.500
if thou givest him not warning,

00:09:58.500 --> 00:10:00.460
his blood will I require.

00:10:00.460 --> 00:10:02.960
require at thine hand.

00:10:02.960 --> 00:10:07.500
Yet, verse 19, if thou warn the wicked,

00:10:07.500 --> 00:10:09.680
and he turn not from his wickedness,

00:10:09.680 --> 00:10:11.180
nor from his wicked way,

00:10:11.180 --> 00:10:14.060
he shall die in his iniquity,

00:10:14.060 --> 00:10:17.900
but thou hast delivered thy soul.

00:10:17.900 --> 00:10:19.500
Not everyone that I've ever warned,

00:10:19.500 --> 00:10:20.940
not everyone that you've ever warned,

00:10:20.940 --> 00:10:23.900
not everyone that I will warn or that you will warn

00:10:23.900 --> 00:10:25.900
will respond to the warning.

00:10:25.900 --> 00:10:27.760
There will be those that will reject,

00:10:27.760 --> 00:10:30.160
that will not believe the warning

00:10:30.160 --> 00:10:32.680
that we're speaking from God.

00:10:32.680 --> 00:10:34.000
And here's what God says,

00:10:34.000 --> 00:10:38.480
but you fulfilled your responsibility as a watchman.

00:10:38.480 --> 00:10:39.320
Why?

00:10:39.320 --> 00:10:41.640
You heard and you delivered.

00:10:41.640 --> 00:10:45.440
And what they do with it is between them and God.

00:10:45.440 --> 00:10:48.400
And he says that that person that did not turn,

00:10:48.400 --> 00:10:50.600
they did not heed the warning,

00:10:50.600 --> 00:10:53.160
that they will die in their iniquity.

00:10:53.160 --> 00:10:54.960
But notice the end of verse number 19,

00:10:54.960 --> 00:10:59.280
but thou hast delivered thy soul.

00:10:59.280 --> 00:11:01.880
Again, verse 20, when a righteous man

00:11:01.880 --> 00:11:05.520
doth turn from his righteousness and commit iniquity,

00:11:05.520 --> 00:11:07.560
and I lay a stumbling block before him,

00:11:07.560 --> 00:11:11.920
he shall die because thou hast not given him warning.

00:11:11.920 --> 00:11:14.320
He shall die in his sin and his righteousness,

00:11:14.320 --> 00:11:16.700
